Yall don’t want to miss tonight! A brand new episode of @thechallenge tonight on CBS 10 pm eastern time!

What were everyone’s thoughts on the cushions and puzzle added to the hall brawl? Definitely an equalizer. Sucks I had to go against my boy Josh but that’s how the game goes. You usually end up competing against your friends in the end. He definitely had his best season yet and in my opinion he would’ve won this final if he was there. He was ready. That was the third time I found myself in the last elimination of the season and man, the pressure and emotions are always high. Personally I was not excited seeing the puzzle and cushions added to hall brawl but I understand for everyone’s safety. 

Call me crazy but I definitely think that my physicality influenced the change to the infamous “hall brawl”. I thought that was a staple that would never be altered. It was a risky strategy to just guess but I figured my first two guesses would be wrong anyways so why waste time studying the puzzle. 
 
I was fortunate enough to get my 3rd hall brawl win(6-1 in eliminations) in the books and make my third final. 
People always saying I need to be humbled, but that’s the thing, I’ve been humbled hundreds of times, but I get right back to it, every time. That’s where my confidence comes from. Extremely thankful for @thechallenge.
Do not allow my confidence to offend your insecurity.
